1 A BILL for an Act to provide for a legislative management study regarding the establishment of a
2 government spending database; and to provide an appropriation.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - GOVERNMENT SPENDING
5 DATABASE. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying
6 the feasibility of the establishment of a government spending database. The study must include:
7 1. A review of the training services necessary for school board members,
8 superintendents, principals, and business managers regarding the government
9 spending database, including best practices, personnel management, financial
10 operations, facility planning, and regulatory compliance.
11 2. The feasibility of establishing a database that compiles the following information for
12 each expenditure:
13 a. The amount paid.
14 b. The payment date.
15 c. The recipient name.
16 d. The paying entity.
17 e. The employee position, if for a personnel payment.
18 f. For a school district, with respect to educational materials:
19 (1) A description of curriculum.
20 (2) The publisher and author of a textbook.
21 (3) A description of software specifications and developer identification.
